config BR2_PACKAGE_EREADER
	bool "ereader"
	select BR2_PACKAGE_DISPLAY_TEST
	select BR2_PACKAGE_BUTTON_TEST
	help
	  E-Reader Application - Full-featured e-reader for Raspberry Pi Zero W.

	  This is the main e-reader application that provides a complete
	  reading experience on the Waveshare 4.2" e-paper display. It includes:

	  Features:
	    - Boot-to-reader: Automatic startup with menu display
	    - Library management: Browse and select books from /books/ directory
	    - Text rendering: Word-wrapped text display with pagination
	    - Page navigation: Turn pages with UP/DOWN buttons
	    - Bookmark support: Automatic position saving to /etc/ereader/bookmarks.txt
	    - Status display: Shows current page, total pages, and book title

	  Hardware Requirements:
	    - Raspberry Pi Zero W (512MB RAM)
	    - Waveshare 4.2" E-Paper Display (400x300, SPI interface)
	    - 5 GPIO buttons (UP, DOWN, SELECT, BACK, MENU)

	  Supported Formats:
	    - Plain text files (.txt)
	    - UTF-8 and ASCII encoding
	    - Maximum file size: 10MB per book

	  Display Specifications:
	    - 400x300 pixel display
	    - 8x16 bitmap font
	    - 14 lines per page
	    - 47 characters per line

	  Usage:
	    - Copy .txt files to /books/ directory
	    - Power on device - boots directly to library menu
	    - Navigate with UP/DOWN buttons
	    - Press SELECT to open a book
	    - Press BACK to return to menu
	    - Reading position is saved automatically

	  This package depends on display-test (EPD driver) and button-test
	  (input system) and integrates them into a cohesive application.

	  https://github.com/yourusername/open-source-ereader
